 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-1v5c","title":"Task 3.5: Implement Popover JavaScript in scripts.rs","description":"# Objective
Add JavaScript functionality for tool badge popovers - show tool details on hover/focus.

## Current State
scripts.rs has theme toggle, search, and encryption JS but no popover handling.

## Required Functionality

### 1. Popover Show/Hide
```javascript
// Tool badge popover controller
(function() {
  const badges = document.querySelectorAll('.tool-badge');

  badges.forEach(badge => {
    const popover = badge.querySelector('.tool-popover');
    if (!popover) return;

    // Show on hover/focus
    badge.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => showPopover(badge, popover));
    badge.addEventListener('focus', () => showPopover(badge, popover));

    // Hide on leave/blur
    badge.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => hidePopover(badge, popover));
    badge.addEventListener('blur', () => hidePopover(badge, popover));

    // Toggle on click/Enter for mobile
    badge.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      togglePopover(badge, popover);
    });
    badge.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
      if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
        e.preventDefault();
        togglePopover(badge, popover);
      }
      if (e.key === 'Escape') {
        hidePopover(badge, popover);
      }
    });
  });

  function showPopover(badge, popover) {
    popover.classList.add('visible');
    badge.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
    positionPopover(badge, popover);
  }

  function hidePopover(badge, popover) {
    popover.classList.remove('visible');
    badge.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
  }

  function togglePopover(badge, popover) {
    const isVisible = popover.classList.contains('visible');
    if (isVisible) {
      hidePopover(badge, popover);
    } else {
      showPopover(badge, popover);
    }
  }

  function positionPopover(badge, popover) {
    // Position below badge, handle viewport overflow
    const rect = badge.getBoundingClientRect();
    const popRect = popover.getBoundingClientRect();

    // Default: below and right-aligned
    let top = rect.bottom + 8;
    let left = rect.left;

    // Flip up if near bottom
    if (top + popRect.height > window.innerHeight - 20) {
      top = rect.top - popRect.height - 8;
    }

    // Flip left if near right edge
    if (left + popRect.width > window.innerWidth - 20) {
      left = rect.right - popRect.width;
    }

    popover.style.top = top + 'px';
    popover.style.left = left + 'px';
  }
})();
```

### 2. Overflow Badge Expansion
```javascript
// Expand "+X more" badge to show all tools
document.querySelectorAll('.tool-overflow').forEach(btn => {
  btn.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const container = btn.closest('.message-header-right');
    container.classList.toggle('expanded');
    // Toggle between "+X more" and "Show less"
    const isExpanded = container.classList.contains('expanded');
    btn.textContent = isExpanded ? 'Less' : btn.dataset.originalText;
  });
});
```

### 3. Close on Outside Click
```javascript
document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
  if (!e.target.closest('.tool-badge')) {
    document.querySelectorAll('.tool-popover.visible').forEach(p => {
      p.classList.remove('visible');
      p.closest('.tool-badge')?.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
    });
  }
});
```

## Integration with scripts.rs
Add to generate_scripts() output, within the existing IIFE structure.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Popover shows on hover (desktop)
- [ ] Popover shows on focus (keyboard)
- [ ] Popover toggles on click (mobile)
- [ ] Escape key closes popover
- [ ] Popover positions correctly (no viewport overflow)
- [ ] aria-expanded updates correctly
- [ ] Overflow badge expansion works
- [ ] Click outside closes popover
- [ ] Works with encrypted exports (after decryption)","notes":"## Search Integration

When user searches within the HTML export:
1. Search should include tool input/output content (stored in data attributes)
2. If search matches tool content, highlight the corresponding badge
3. Badge should pulse/glow when its content matches search

```javascript
// In Search.search() function, also search tool content
document.querySelectorAll('.tool-badge').forEach(badge => {
    const toolInput = badge.dataset.toolInput || '';
    const toolOutput = badge.dataset.toolOutput || '';
    const fullContent = toolInput + ' ' + toolOutput;

    if (fullContent.toLowerCase().includes(query.toLowerCase())) {
        badge.classList.add('search-match');
    } else {
        badge.classList.remove('search-match');
    }
});
```

## Print Mode Handling

Popovers don't work in print, so badges need alternative display:

```javascript
// Before print, expand badges to show names
window.addEventListener('beforeprint', () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('.tool-badge').forEach(badge => {
        badge.classList.add('print-expanded');
    });
});

// After print, restore
window.addEventListener('afterprint', () => {
    document.querySelectorAll('.tool-badge').forEach(badge => {
        badge.classList.remove('print-expanded');
    });
});
```

CSS for print-expanded:
```css
.tool-badge.print-expanded::after {
    content: attr(data-tool-name);
    margin-left: 4px;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
}

@media print {
    .tool-badge {
        width: auto;
        padding: 2px 6px;
    }
    .tool-badge.print-expanded::after {
        display: inline;
    }
}
```

## Mobile Touch Considerations

1. First tap shows popover
2. Tap outside dismisses
3. Tap same badge toggles
4. Swipe down on popover dismisses (optional gesture)

```javascript
let touchStartY = 0;
popover.addEventListener('touchstart', (e) => {
    touchStartY = e.touches[0].clientY;
});
popover.addEventListener('touchmove', (e) => {
    const deltaY = e.touches[0].clientY - touchStartY;
    if (deltaY > 50) {
        hidePopover(badge, popover);
    }
});
